WEBVTT

00:08.056 --> 00:11.320
[SIRENS WAILING]

00:11.451 --> 00:14.236
REPORTER: Protestors engaged
again with police

00:14.323 --> 00:16.195
during a series
of violent clashes

00:16.282 --> 00:17.979
throughout the city tonight.[CROWD CLAMORING]

00:18.458 --> 00:20.938
REPORTER: Denying all charges
of bribery and extortion,

00:21.548 --> 00:22.810
the mayor's office is now

00:22.897 --> 00:25.160
urging residents
to stay off the streets

00:25.421 --> 00:28.381
as curfews are implemented
in the downtown area.

00:28.729 --> 00:32.341
In the wake of countless reports
of arson and vandalism,

00:32.472 --> 00:34.561
the Governor
is threatening to declare

00:34.648 --> 00:35.910
a state of emergency,

00:36.215 --> 00:38.782
giving her the ability
to bring in the National Guard.

00:38.869 --> 00:40.219
[SIREN WAILS]

00:41.872 --> 00:44.440
[INDISTINCT CHATTER
OVER POLICE RADIO]

00:45.441 --> 00:47.313
HALE: This is Hale.
I've arrived at the scene.

00:51.534 --> 00:55.886
[ALARMS BLARING]

01:05.635 --> 01:10.031
[SIRENS WAILING]

01:12.425 --> 01:14.383
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:18.213 --> 01:19.997
[FIRE CRACKLING]

01:27.483 --> 01:28.919
HALE:
I don't see the police officer,

01:29.006 --> 01:29.964
I'm going in.

01:30.530 --> 01:31.879
RICK: Well, maybe
he went in a little bit early

01:32.009 --> 01:33.054
to get a head start on things?

01:33.228 --> 01:34.534
It's gonna be
a busy night for everyone.

01:35.622 --> 01:36.623
HALE: All I'm saying is,

01:37.493 --> 01:39.234
it'd be nice
to have someone to...

01:40.322 --> 01:41.845
keep the homeless at bay.

01:42.194 --> 01:43.630
How's things looking out there?

01:43.847 --> 01:46.676
Oh, no.
The crazies are out tonight.

01:50.158 --> 01:51.638
Be careful out there,
Officer Hale.

01:51.899 --> 01:53.292
[THUDDING]

01:53.814 --> 01:55.120
HALE: Looks like
our guys barely had time

01:55.207 --> 01:57.426
to put this out
before running off to the next.

01:59.559 --> 02:01.038
The whole city is a mess.

02:01.126 --> 02:02.127
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

02:02.388 --> 02:04.129
I'll be able to tell you
how it happened

02:04.694 --> 02:05.652
right after this.

02:06.392 --> 02:07.828
[DEVICE BEEPING]

02:07.915 --> 02:09.134
How many people died?

02:10.091 --> 02:11.919
There were at least
three fatalities

02:12.006 --> 02:12.876
the other night.

02:14.008 --> 02:15.923
HALE: Probably due
to some kind of trip stove,

02:16.010 --> 02:17.142
or something like that.

02:19.535 --> 02:20.449
Yeah, well,

02:20.928 --> 02:22.451
that building should've
been demolished years ago.

02:29.632 --> 02:31.678
Picking up traces
of some type of accelerant.

02:31.808 --> 02:32.896
[DEVICE BEEPS]

02:32.983 --> 02:34.289
This was intentional.

02:36.378 --> 02:39.076
[GASPS] What the hell, man?

02:39.164 --> 02:40.295
Did you just get here?

02:40.600 --> 02:42.471
What? What?[CLANKING]

02:46.040 --> 02:47.520
THOMAS: Thought
I cleared everybody out.

02:49.043 --> 02:51.045
Probably just a squatter.
I'll run 'em off.

02:51.437 --> 02:53.090
Yeah. You go do that.

02:53.874 --> 02:55.005
I'll be right here.

02:58.444 --> 03:00.054
[DEVICE BEEPING]

03:07.017 --> 03:09.368
Hello? Anybody in here?

03:14.242 --> 03:18.203
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES][CAT YOWLS]

03:18.638 --> 03:19.552
Shit.

03:19.682 --> 03:20.596
HALE:
Everything all right up there?

03:21.423 --> 03:22.468
It's just a cat.

03:24.252 --> 03:25.949
[SCOFFS LIGHTLY]

03:31.694 --> 03:32.652
THOMAS: Hey, wise ass.

03:34.480 --> 03:36.003
This building is condemned.

03:38.092 --> 03:39.224
Time to go.

03:44.272 --> 03:45.230
Fuck.

03:48.624 --> 03:51.236
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

03:55.544 --> 03:56.893
"Acheronta"?

04:00.723 --> 04:02.203
[THUMPING]

04:08.818 --> 04:10.080
You okay up there?

04:23.224 --> 04:25.400
Hey. Everything okay up there?

04:25.574 --> 04:27.054
[GROANS]

04:32.189 --> 04:33.669
Fuck!

04:35.976 --> 04:37.064
HALE: What the--

04:37.630 --> 04:41.198
[PENSIVE MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

04:41.286 --> 04:45.028
[PANTING]

04:52.340 --> 04:53.733
[GASPS]

05:00.174 --> 05:01.567
What--

05:03.873 --> 05:05.266
No!

05:08.922 --> 05:13.622
[EXCLAIMS, GRUNTS] No, no!
I gotta get out of here!

05:15.102 --> 05:18.671
[GROANS]

05:19.367 --> 05:23.110
[GROANS, SCREAMS]

05:24.981 --> 05:26.113
[GLASS SHATTERS]

05:27.810 --> 05:29.899
[SCREAMS]

05:30.073 --> 05:31.727
DAVID: Superos.

05:34.774 --> 05:36.863
WOMAN: [SCREAMING]
Help! Somebody!

05:37.820 --> 05:40.606
Help us! Help![SCREAMS]

05:43.086 --> 05:45.654
[HALE CRYING OUT]

05:55.795 --> 05:57.362
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONCLUDES]

05:57.492 --> 06:00.103
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

06:15.467 --> 06:20.776
[SMART WATCH RINGS][UPBEAT MUSIC CONCLUDES]

06:23.300 --> 06:24.911
[PANTS] Hey, Dad.

06:25.041 --> 06:26.434
What was your time?

06:26.521 --> 06:28.523
Uh, 17:20.

06:28.610 --> 06:30.699
PATRICK: That's 20 seconds
off your best time.

06:31.265 --> 06:32.832
[CHUCKLES]
You better pick it up.

06:32.962 --> 06:34.616
It's just been a tough week,
that's all, Dad.

06:34.834 --> 06:36.139
PATRICK: No, I understand that.

06:36.226 --> 06:39.882
Listen. I'm gonna make you
some of the pancakes

06:39.969 --> 06:41.884
that your mom
used to make from scratch,

06:42.319 --> 06:44.844
and you're gonna love it.
You know how important it is to

06:44.931 --> 06:48.151
get a good power breakfast in,
you know what I'm saying?

06:48.456 --> 06:50.545
[CHUCKLES] I'd love to, but I--

06:51.154 --> 06:52.199
Look, I don't think
I'm gonna have much time.

06:52.286 --> 06:53.461
I can't be late today.

06:54.114 --> 06:55.289
PATRICK: You're gonna crush it.

06:55.376 --> 06:56.638
LOU: Hey, Daddy, um...

06:57.030 --> 06:59.032
you've done so much for me
since Mom passed,

06:59.162 --> 07:00.425
letting me stay and all.

07:00.860 --> 07:03.079
I'm getting my first check
in a couple weeks, and, um...

07:03.863 --> 07:05.342
I wanna... [SIGHS]

07:05.430 --> 07:06.822
I wanna chip in a little.

07:07.301 --> 07:08.258
Your first check?

07:08.694 --> 07:09.825
What are you talking about?
I want all your checks.

07:11.218 --> 07:12.698
What are you talking about?

07:12.785 --> 07:14.482
You're my daughter,
and I love you.

07:15.048 --> 07:16.963
And... and, by the way...

07:17.703 --> 07:19.356
Protestors
were out in force on--

07:19.444 --> 07:20.662
PATRICK: One second, honey,
I'm listening to the news.

07:20.749 --> 07:22.185
...for the third
consecutive year.

07:22.534 --> 07:25.493
Injuries and hospitalizations
have been reported

07:25.580 --> 07:29.192
during what initially started
as non-violent protests

07:29.279 --> 07:30.933
regarding city corruption

07:31.020 --> 07:33.501
following several
high-profile cases.

07:33.632 --> 07:35.416
PATRICK:
Should be careful out there.

07:35.634 --> 07:37.287
It looks like it's gonna
be pretty rough tonight.

07:39.464 --> 07:40.769
No, no, no.
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

07:43.250 --> 07:44.817
I'm not gonna be
anywhere near what's happening.

07:45.731 --> 07:47.820
I'm still in training,
so they're not sending me out,

07:48.951 --> 07:54.348
so, uh, you don't have to worry.
[PANTS]

07:55.828 --> 07:57.438
Besides, I'm your daughter,

07:57.656 --> 07:59.788
the daily run
will be our shadowboxing.[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

08:00.049 --> 08:01.398
All that training growing up?

08:02.269 --> 08:03.400
It didn't go to waste.

08:03.488 --> 08:05.881
Don't forget about
the Jiu Jitsu. Okay?

08:05.968 --> 08:08.014
You were kicking
little boys' asses

08:08.101 --> 08:09.232
when you were eight years old.

08:09.450 --> 08:11.974
You're amazing.
You're unstoppable!

08:12.061 --> 08:14.716
You're gonna be working
with the Fire Department, okay?

08:14.977 --> 08:16.413
It can get rough out there.

08:16.501 --> 08:18.459
Just be careful,
is all I'm saying.

08:18.894 --> 08:22.245
[LOU PANTS] Hey, by the way,
it's Wednesday, isn't it?

08:22.463 --> 08:23.856
Don't you have poker
with your buddies at the club?

08:23.986 --> 08:26.249
You know, I actually got
all the guys from the precinct,

08:26.336 --> 08:27.686
all the retired guys,
coming over.

08:27.773 --> 08:29.688
I just--
I miss their smell so much.

08:29.818 --> 08:30.906
Look, I gotta go.

08:31.080 --> 08:32.952
Uh, I can't be late.
I'll see you soon, okay?

08:33.039 --> 08:34.519
All right.
I'll see you soon, honey.

08:35.911 --> 08:40.525
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING][DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

08:40.699 --> 08:42.962
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

08:43.092 --> 08:44.311
[LOU PANTS]

08:44.441 --> 08:46.095
LANA:
Authorities are still searching

08:46.182 --> 08:47.357
for the perpetrators

08:47.749 --> 08:50.752
who stole countless weapons
from the Museum of Antiquity.

08:51.448 --> 08:54.451
City officials are claiming
outside instigators

08:54.626 --> 08:57.890
are coming in and hijacking
this peaceful movement.

08:58.412 --> 09:02.329
I am Lana Larkin from KIL 57.

09:04.766 --> 09:06.333
Hey, I was watching that,
grasshopper.

09:06.463 --> 09:08.727
[CHUCKLES] Hi!Hopper. [KISSES]

09:09.815 --> 09:11.425
This smells very good.Yes.

09:12.426 --> 09:13.514
We're gonna have a feast.

09:13.688 --> 09:15.298
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

09:15.516 --> 09:17.605
All right, let me get this.
Patrick.

09:20.695 --> 09:22.218
No, no, no, I--

09:22.479 --> 09:24.873
Thank you, man. I'm retired.
Appreciate it.

09:25.613 --> 09:27.572
Yeah, I'm taking it easy now.
No, no, no.

09:27.659 --> 09:28.834
Thank you, though.[BEEPS]

09:30.879 --> 09:31.967
Proud of me?

09:32.141 --> 09:33.926
I don't believe it for a second.
I really don't.

09:34.100 --> 09:36.493
[CHUCKLES] Okay.
So I have to take a shower.

09:36.668 --> 09:37.843
PATRICK: All right.Hmm.

09:38.017 --> 09:40.149
And, in honor
of your retirement,

09:40.976 --> 09:43.283
I will eat this bacon
in the shower. It is so good.

09:43.588 --> 09:45.024
So you're not gonna
actually eat?

09:45.981 --> 09:48.244
The world does not need
a hangry paramedic!

09:48.505 --> 09:51.160
[SIRENS WAILING]

09:52.814 --> 09:54.686
LANA:
This place is disgusting.

09:54.903 --> 09:56.165
Stop![CAR TIRES SCREECHING]

09:56.426 --> 09:58.603
Did you even get
a shot of the exterior?

09:59.038 --> 10:00.517
I want something that shouts

10:00.605 --> 10:03.129
"Inner-city community
crying for help."

10:03.346 --> 10:05.871
CAMERAMAN: Uh, yeah. It's got
"Pulitzer" written all over it.

10:06.088 --> 10:07.437
Oh, fuck off.

10:07.829 --> 10:09.875
[GRUMBLES]I got it.

10:10.005 --> 10:11.311
How do I look?

10:13.008 --> 10:14.009
Beautiful.

10:14.357 --> 10:16.882
Christ. Try not to choke
to death on a fucking donut.

10:18.318 --> 10:19.972
[SCOFFS] Okay.

10:20.755 --> 10:21.756
And...[CAMERA BEEPS]

10:22.061 --> 10:23.236
...rolling.

10:23.758 --> 10:26.718
Four, three, two, one.

10:26.805 --> 10:27.806
Five years ago,

10:28.154 --> 10:31.200
I reported just outside
this very apartment building

10:31.461 --> 10:34.421
as a fire ravaged
this inner-city community

10:34.508 --> 10:36.118
and caused the horrific deaths

10:36.205 --> 10:37.990
of an entire family
trapped inside.

10:38.643 --> 10:39.905
And earlier this week,

10:39.992 --> 10:43.212
this same building
was set on fire yet again,

10:43.430 --> 10:46.651
claiming the lives of several
in the homeless community--

10:46.781 --> 10:48.696
another tragic reminder

10:48.827 --> 10:51.220
of the lawlessness
now gripping this city.

10:51.394 --> 10:52.352
Stay with us

10:52.831 --> 10:55.398
as we offer updates
from behind police barricades.

10:56.095 --> 10:59.359
This is reporter Lana Larkin,
signing off.

10:59.707 --> 11:01.056
[CAMERA BEEPS]

11:01.491 --> 11:03.885
The proper term is "unhoused"
or "people without housing".

11:04.016 --> 11:06.105
You're not supposed to say
"homeless" anymore.

11:06.192 --> 11:07.976
It's the same thing,
you fat fuck.

11:08.281 --> 11:09.369
Well, it's just what I've heard!

11:09.586 --> 11:11.371
Okay, you know what?
Fine, "unhoused".

11:13.112 --> 11:15.201
[SIGHS, SNIFFS]

11:15.767 --> 11:17.899
[CHUCKLES, GASPS]

11:20.032 --> 11:23.078
LANA: Watch out![CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

11:23.296 --> 11:25.080
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

11:25.254 --> 11:28.823
[INDISTINCT CHATTER
OVER POLICE RADIO]

11:33.698 --> 11:35.134
RUSSO:
You think he drove himself here?

11:36.526 --> 11:37.876
All right, he kills a cop,

11:38.615 --> 11:40.052
drops the car here,

11:41.096 --> 11:42.445
and puts the body
in the front seat.

11:42.532 --> 11:43.490
Who does that?

11:45.579 --> 11:46.711
"Superos"?

11:48.582 --> 11:50.236
Does anyone know
what the fuck this means?

11:59.811 --> 12:01.073
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONCLUDES]

12:02.422 --> 12:03.728
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

12:14.042 --> 12:17.698
PATRICK: Wow, look at you!
[CLAPPING]

12:18.177 --> 12:19.526
You look great.
You look beautiful.

12:19.656 --> 12:20.832
How's training going?

12:21.267 --> 12:23.791
Yeah, it's good. Um, you know,
I passed all my certifications,

12:23.878 --> 12:25.271
so I'm just waiting
for the green light.

12:25.358 --> 12:26.794
Your mom would be proud of you.

12:27.316 --> 12:28.665
I want you to go--
You gotta eat.

12:28.753 --> 12:30.406
Okay, yes.Don't forget to eat.

12:30.493 --> 12:31.756
Please.Thank you, Dad.

12:31.930 --> 12:32.974
Go knock 'em dead...LOU: Love you, Dad!

12:33.061 --> 12:34.236
...and then revive 'em again!

12:34.367 --> 12:36.325
And just keep, like,
an endless loop.

12:36.586 --> 12:38.850
I love you!LOU: Love you, too!

12:40.112 --> 12:45.465
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

13:09.837 --> 13:14.059
[ALARM RINGING]

13:14.929 --> 13:17.802
[RICK ANNOUNCING INDISTINCTLY]

13:24.983 --> 13:28.551
[FIREMEN CLAMORING]

13:49.137 --> 13:50.747
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONCLUDES]

13:50.878 --> 13:52.445
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

13:52.793 --> 13:53.968
RICK: O'Connor, a moment?

13:56.188 --> 13:58.668
Walk with me.Chief.

13:58.930 --> 14:01.019
There's no use crying
over spilled milk, am I right?

14:01.889 --> 14:03.586
Sir?No hard feelings?

14:04.674 --> 14:07.852
Uh. You're talking about
how you tried to fail me?

14:08.417 --> 14:09.984
Hey.MAN: Thanks.

14:10.158 --> 14:11.159
Did I?

14:11.507 --> 14:12.900
Look, in case it wasn't clear,

14:13.031 --> 14:14.771
I'm not entirely sure
you belong here.

14:14.946 --> 14:17.296
Respectfully, sir,
I would disagree.

14:17.949 --> 14:18.993
Well, you know what?

14:19.907 --> 14:21.082
The fact of the matter is,

14:21.169 --> 14:22.779
there's only two kinds
of people in this world.

14:22.867 --> 14:23.911
Those who know how to think

14:23.998 --> 14:25.217
and act when the shit
hits the fan,

14:25.304 --> 14:27.132
and those who don't.
I think you're the latter.

14:27.349 --> 14:28.524
And it's nothing
to be ashamed of.

14:28.655 --> 14:29.917
Some people
are just built that way.

14:30.004 --> 14:31.876
It... it's not
that I froze, Chief.

14:31.963 --> 14:33.660
I believed that the patient
could be saved.

14:33.747 --> 14:34.791
RICK: You're overthinking.

14:35.053 --> 14:36.924
That costs lives,
regardless of the reason.

14:37.011 --> 14:38.360
Okay? It's called triage.

14:38.578 --> 14:40.014
You treat, and you move on.

14:40.145 --> 14:42.582
That's the job, O'Connor,
whether you like it or not.

14:42.712 --> 14:44.323
You spent too much time
with the mother.

14:44.410 --> 14:47.152
You left those kids alone,
unchecked, in the back.

14:47.282 --> 14:48.196
I thought there was a chance.

14:48.631 --> 14:50.982
She had injuries
incompatible with life. Period!

14:51.460 --> 14:53.375
And you sure as shit don't know
what those kids had,

14:53.462 --> 14:55.900
because you didn't check.
You left that for me to do.

14:56.291 --> 14:57.814
And that is a hell of a way

14:57.945 --> 14:59.207
for you
to tackle your practicum.

14:59.338 --> 15:00.774
That wasn't my intent, Chief.

15:00.992 --> 15:03.255
[SIGHS] Look.

15:06.432 --> 15:07.476
You see a fire,

15:08.521 --> 15:10.653
you either go towards it,
or you run away.

15:11.350 --> 15:13.352
How you make that decision,
that choice,

15:13.569 --> 15:15.354
that determines
if you belong here.

15:16.659 --> 15:18.183
You're gonna have to make
that choice today.

15:19.662 --> 15:20.620
I'm going out?

15:21.012 --> 15:22.535
It was determined to let you
out of your training.

15:22.752 --> 15:24.885
For my part? I'm watching you.

15:25.494 --> 15:26.931
LOU: That's great, Chief!
You won't regret it,

15:27.061 --> 15:27.932
I promise you.RICK: All right.

15:28.323 --> 15:29.890
Don't make me come out there
and check up on you.

15:30.021 --> 15:30.891
This is it.

15:31.152 --> 15:32.458
Your bus is already late
for the dance.

15:33.502 --> 15:34.677
You're gonna be riding
with Jason.

15:35.330 --> 15:37.245
Fifteen years on the job,
you can do a lot worse.

15:37.332 --> 15:38.638
Keep your eyes open, take notes

15:38.725 --> 15:40.074
and see how it's done
by one of the best.

15:40.292 --> 15:41.249
Right.

15:41.510 --> 15:43.208
Hey, Chief,
you still looking for Hale?

15:44.426 --> 15:45.427
We're working on it.

15:45.732 --> 15:47.560
Haven't seen him
since last night's fire.

15:49.257 --> 15:50.911
So I get you
for your first shift

15:50.998 --> 15:52.782
without any training wheels?
You ready for this?

15:52.913 --> 15:54.045
Yep, ready.

15:54.567 --> 15:56.134
We can't have any fuck-ups,
not today.

15:56.699 --> 15:57.918
The shit is hitting the fan.

15:58.484 --> 16:00.616
Got it.Oh...

16:03.793 --> 16:06.057
Is it true the Chief failed you
at the Academy?

16:06.144 --> 16:07.058
LOU: It's complicated.

16:07.493 --> 16:09.974
JASON: [SCOFFS, LAUGHS]
Wonderful.

16:12.019 --> 16:12.977
Okay.

16:13.978 --> 16:15.022
Now, I'm guessing
no one's told you about

16:15.109 --> 16:16.893
rule number one?What rule?

16:16.981 --> 16:19.113
You need to put on
your game face before going out.

16:19.200 --> 16:20.549
It's like your war face,

16:20.767 --> 16:22.812
but with your mouth closed
and breathing through your nose

16:22.899 --> 16:25.554
so that nothing from a patient
ends up in your mouth. Now,

16:26.251 --> 16:28.340
the last crew's a little behind,
and we still need to refuel,

16:28.427 --> 16:29.645
so we're gonna
have to hustle out of here.

16:29.950 --> 16:31.952
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

16:36.783 --> 16:38.611
[RADIO STATIC CRACKLES]

16:39.264 --> 16:40.439
The emergency channel's
all filled up.

16:40.526 --> 16:43.703
I can't hear anything.
Switching over to 2-B.

16:44.573 --> 16:46.445
We are ready to...

16:46.532 --> 16:47.576
[RADIO BEEPS]...go.

16:47.968 --> 16:49.013
RICK: Medic Three.

16:50.449 --> 16:51.363
Go ahead.

16:51.928 --> 16:53.582
RICK: There's a possible
stabbing of one male party.

16:53.713 --> 16:55.410
Proceed to 412 Broadway.

16:55.497 --> 16:56.933
You'll find police
already at the scene.

16:57.064 --> 16:59.110
Copy, we're en route.

16:59.719 --> 17:01.503
This should take us
pretty close to Old Town.

17:02.287 --> 17:04.376
How close, exactly?Just across the river.

17:05.116 --> 17:06.856
Hmm. I grew up
not far from there.

17:07.640 --> 17:09.468
We're seeing
the Devil's Punch Bowl, I guess?

17:15.778 --> 17:16.910
[SIREN WAILING]

17:16.997 --> 17:18.346
REPORTER:
Bridges in and out of the city

17:18.433 --> 17:20.392
are now officially closed
to the public

17:20.522 --> 17:22.481
as violence reaches
historic levels.

17:24.787 --> 17:27.442
In yet another surprising
turn of events,

17:27.703 --> 17:29.662
the Chief of Police
announced his department

17:29.749 --> 17:33.057
is undertaking a series
of internal investigations,

17:33.187 --> 17:34.449
aimed at rooting out

17:34.580 --> 17:36.886
what many see
as blatant acts of corruption

17:36.973 --> 17:40.151
among rank-and-file members
of the City's law enforcement.

17:40.412 --> 17:43.980
[SIREN WAILING]

17:44.633 --> 17:47.158
[CROWD CLAMORING]

17:51.597 --> 17:53.077
[SIREN WAILING]

18:03.870 --> 18:06.438
Saint Joseph's code yellow,
only taking life-threatenings.

18:07.047 --> 18:08.048
What about Julian?

18:08.179 --> 18:09.745
LOU: Nope,
they're at capacity.

18:14.185 --> 18:15.664
This is where
everything went down last night.

18:19.581 --> 18:21.888
Okay. Here we go.

18:22.018 --> 18:23.150
Let's move.Okay.

18:27.372 --> 18:30.375
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

18:30.592 --> 18:32.899
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

18:33.595 --> 18:35.597
Ma'am, my name is Lou
with Seattle Fire.

18:35.771 --> 18:36.729
Do you wanna tell me
what's happening here?

18:37.077 --> 18:39.123
Do you have any pain?
Anything bothering you?

18:39.601 --> 18:40.820
Let me get that
fixed up for you.

18:40.907 --> 18:42.430
JASON: Need to put this on you
nice and gently.

18:43.083 --> 18:44.476
We'll get you
all fixed up here, okay?

18:44.606 --> 18:47.566
LOU: You're okay. Good, good.
Yeah? All right.

18:48.480 --> 18:50.917
Just real gentle, okay?JASON: You're doing great.

18:52.614 --> 18:53.876
Sir? Please,

18:54.268 --> 18:56.662
have a seat right here
on the sidewalk. Yeah.

18:56.792 --> 18:57.706
I'll help you down.

18:57.880 --> 18:59.404
My name's Jason
from Seattle Fire.

18:59.665 --> 19:00.709
How you doing?

19:01.057 --> 19:03.625
[SCREAMING]

19:06.411 --> 19:08.064
You hear that?Take a look.

19:08.674 --> 19:11.155
See if there's anyone else
who needs some help. Go.

19:11.372 --> 19:12.939
Okay. I have to check
on other people.

19:27.301 --> 19:29.042
JASON: All right.
You're gonna be okay.

19:32.828 --> 19:33.916
[GASPS]

19:37.877 --> 19:39.095
[CLATTERING]

19:48.627 --> 19:53.849
[FIRE CRACKLING]

19:59.203 --> 20:01.857
Seattle Fire paramedic.
Is anyone in need of assistance?

20:09.213 --> 20:12.172
Seattle Fire paramedic!
Is anyone in need of assistance?

20:27.666 --> 20:30.016
[GASPS] Oh, my God!

20:34.499 --> 20:35.935
Jason, Jason! Do you copy?

20:36.022 --> 20:37.241
You're gonna wanna see this.
Get over here!

20:38.503 --> 20:40.809
Jason! [GASPS]

20:42.594 --> 20:43.986
I don't know
what the hell this is!

20:44.160 --> 20:46.032
Jason. Jason!
I need you here, man!

20:46.119 --> 20:47.425
Where-- Jason--

20:47.642 --> 20:51.211
Sir! Sir! Sir! Jason![GROANS]

20:51.385 --> 20:52.952
LOU: Jason, I got a man down!
Where are you?

20:53.039 --> 20:56.042
Sir, sir, sir. Sir, sir!
Come on!

20:56.129 --> 20:58.262
Jason! Jason,
I gotta start CPR, okay?

20:58.784 --> 21:01.134
[WHISPERS]
Okay, one, two, three...

21:01.221 --> 21:04.006
Jason, I need you here!
Do you copy? Get over here!

21:04.180 --> 21:06.705
One, two, three.
One, two, three.

21:06.835 --> 21:08.402
One, two, three...

21:08.533 --> 21:09.882
Jason, do you have it?

21:09.969 --> 21:12.363
[PANTS]

21:13.581 --> 21:18.238
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

21:18.630 --> 21:21.763
[INDISTINCT CHATTER][POLICE RADIO CRACKLING]

21:22.416 --> 21:23.809
I got it, thanks.

21:25.767 --> 21:27.465
RUSSO: Hi.Hi.

21:27.813 --> 21:29.336
I'm Detective Stan Russo.

21:30.076 --> 21:31.947
Lucy O'Connor.
You can call me "Lou".

21:32.121 --> 21:33.427
Okay, Lou.

21:34.646 --> 21:37.997
Uh, so she was some kinda,
like, reporter, right?

21:38.432 --> 21:39.520
RUSSO: She was.

21:40.434 --> 21:43.132
The guy you saved
was her cameraman. Nice work.

21:43.872 --> 21:45.309
Yeah, well,
whoever did that twisted shit

21:45.396 --> 21:46.658
is not right in the head.

21:46.919 --> 21:47.876
Yeah. Well, I've been told

21:47.963 --> 21:50.052
he's been put
into an induced coma.

21:51.837 --> 21:54.187
Otherwise, he might be able
to tell us what happened here.

21:56.058 --> 21:57.277
Do you think he'll recover?

21:58.147 --> 21:59.366
LOU: I mean,
he was in pretty bad shape

21:59.453 --> 22:00.541
when they took him away.

22:00.846 --> 22:02.500
I think it'd be a miracle
if he made it the night.

22:07.200 --> 22:09.898
Hey, listen. I know you guys are
gonna be running calls all day.

22:09.985 --> 22:11.944
Yeah. Detective, um, I gotta
get back to my partner.

22:12.074 --> 22:13.032
I'll be quick.

22:14.468 --> 22:15.817
All right, when you arrived
at the scene,

22:15.948 --> 22:17.036
was there anyone else there?

22:17.776 --> 22:18.733
Um...

22:20.126 --> 22:22.302
no, no, I just--
Look, I told the officer--

22:22.563 --> 22:24.173
Just a bunch of injured people
in the area.

22:25.871 --> 22:28.613
Hey, uh, by the way,
can I ask you something?

22:28.917 --> 22:30.049
Go ahead.

22:32.617 --> 22:33.966
What in the hell

22:34.358 --> 22:36.142
is that thing
sticking out of her mouth?

22:38.144 --> 22:40.364
It's supposed to be
a medieval torture device.

22:41.103 --> 22:44.019
It's from several items
that were stolen from a museum.

22:45.238 --> 22:47.066
It's, uh, called
the "Pear of Anguish".

22:47.719 --> 22:50.112
[DUMPSTER RUMBLES]

22:51.723 --> 22:55.030
[OMINOUS MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

22:56.423 --> 22:57.337
Again?

22:58.077 --> 22:59.600
Can anyone tell me
what this means?

23:00.296 --> 23:02.386
That's Latin. Yeah.

23:03.996 --> 23:05.258
It means, like...

23:06.390 --> 23:08.870
"If I cannot".Thanks.

23:09.654 --> 23:10.872
Sure, whatever.

23:13.571 --> 23:14.528
All right, guys, listen up!

23:15.050 --> 23:16.704
All right, no one moves
this fast without messing up!

23:16.791 --> 23:17.749
All right? We gotta hustle

23:18.010 --> 23:19.446
before this turns
into a shit-show. Let's go!

23:19.968 --> 23:22.362
You're with me.[OMINOUS MUSIC CONCLUDES]

23:22.754 --> 23:25.670
Tilt to the side for me there.
Great. Thank you.

23:26.497 --> 23:31.589
WOMAN: Hey, stop. Stop, there.[CAR HORN HONKING]

23:31.806 --> 23:34.505
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

23:34.853 --> 23:36.028
Hey, where's your partner?

23:38.639 --> 23:40.336
I'm just gonna apply
slight pressure, all right?

23:40.554 --> 23:41.468
Good.

23:43.035 --> 23:44.297
Hey.
You look a little hurt, huh?

23:45.690 --> 23:47.822
Listen, while this nice lady
patches you up,

23:47.953 --> 23:48.910
can you tell me what happened?

23:49.215 --> 23:51.913
They... they just...
just started hitting me.

23:52.523 --> 23:54.133
LOU: Okay.
It looks like we've got

23:54.220 --> 23:56.701
a large laceration
in the right abdominal side.

23:56.831 --> 23:59.268
I'm gonna need to take
a look at this, sir. Okay?

23:59.921 --> 24:02.620
All right, I'm just gonna take
a quick look, all right?

24:04.926 --> 24:08.974
[CHILLING MUSIC PLAYING][LOU GASPS]

24:09.409 --> 24:11.324
RUSSO: "Flectere"?
Do you know what that means?

24:14.109 --> 24:15.459
Sir, do you know
who did this to you?

24:15.763 --> 24:16.721
Have you seen this woman?

24:17.983 --> 24:20.072
Have you seen her?I didn't see nothing.

24:20.246 --> 24:21.203
Just--Get away. Get away!

24:21.290 --> 24:22.291
LOU: Sir--Get away.

24:22.378 --> 24:24.076
Get away from me!Okay. Okay, sir.

24:24.380 --> 24:26.034
MAN: [GRUMBLES]
Don't touch me!

24:27.471 --> 24:31.039
[CHILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

24:31.823 --> 24:33.520
Wouldn't let me touch him.
I don't know.

24:33.999 --> 24:36.088
Well, these-- these guys get
harassed all the time.

24:36.262 --> 24:38.699
Yeah. If we took
that guy to the hospital,

24:38.786 --> 24:41.049
they'd just give him an aspirin
and let him go.

24:41.833 --> 24:44.357
You're not wrong about that.Chief, we're clear here.

24:44.792 --> 24:45.793
RICK: [OVER RADIO] Roger that.

24:51.016 --> 24:52.234
We're low on supplies.

24:52.800 --> 24:54.976
RICK: Copy. Head on back
and restock the ambulance.

24:55.237 --> 24:57.283
Do you think
that was Latin on the wall?

24:57.457 --> 24:59.372
No, it was, yeah.

25:00.416 --> 25:02.854
Any chance you know
what "superos"means?

25:02.984 --> 25:04.551
That's Latin, too, right?

25:06.901 --> 25:08.773
It means, "the gods".

25:10.775 --> 25:11.950
That's interesting.

25:15.562 --> 25:17.433
So, all this reading,
is it, like, a...

25:17.738 --> 25:18.696
is it a hobby?

25:19.000 --> 25:20.959
Majored in a dead language.

25:21.481 --> 25:23.091
Ended up doing my thesis on it.

25:23.309 --> 25:26.181
Everybody thought
it'd be useless, but, hey...

25:28.140 --> 25:29.228
Oh, Latin?

25:30.446 --> 25:31.926
I can barely speak English.

25:32.187 --> 25:33.493
Yeah. And Mandarin.

25:34.625 --> 25:36.235
Grew up in Chinatown as a kid.

25:36.322 --> 25:38.106
Worked at Mr. Wong's Palace.

25:38.672 --> 25:39.934
RUSSO: Oh, I know that place.

25:40.021 --> 25:42.241
Yeah. That's how
I picked up the language.

25:42.850 --> 25:45.200
Then, out of nowhere,
Dad moved us to River Falls.

25:46.114 --> 25:47.246
RUSSO: That's quite the upgrade.

25:47.333 --> 25:48.682
LOU: I always liked it
in Chinatown--

25:48.769 --> 25:49.727
More sense of community.

25:49.814 --> 25:50.684
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

25:50.771 --> 25:52.860
There's still people inside!

25:53.034 --> 25:54.688
[SCREAMS]

25:56.081 --> 25:57.561
DAVID: Si nequeo.

25:58.083 --> 25:59.127
LOU: We good?

26:01.869 --> 26:05.525
[CHILLING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

26:06.134 --> 26:07.788
DAVID: Flectere.

26:18.277 --> 26:20.714
RUSSO: Ah, these guys keep
coming out of the woodwork.

26:26.459 --> 26:31.377
[CHILLING MUSIC CONCLUDES]

26:45.434 --> 26:46.958
I've never seen it so empty.

26:47.915 --> 26:50.135
JASON: You should shower,

26:50.309 --> 26:51.789
and grab a bite to eat
and get some rest.

26:52.267 --> 26:53.399
It's gonna be a late night.

26:54.095 --> 26:56.097
I'll restock, refuel
and be back in an hour.

26:56.271 --> 26:57.446
LOU: Thanks, Jason.

26:58.360 --> 27:00.798
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

27:08.066 --> 27:09.241
LOU: Jason! Jason! Do you copy?

27:09.371 --> 27:10.634
You're gonna wanna see this!
Get over here!

27:10.764 --> 27:11.809
You're gonna wanna see this!
Get over here...

27:11.939 --> 27:13.767
Jason! Jason...

27:14.550 --> 27:16.161
Jason, do you copy?
I need you here!

27:16.291 --> 27:17.641
I don't know
what the fuck I'm seeing.

27:17.771 --> 27:18.903
What the fuck I'm seeing.

27:18.990 --> 27:20.818
What the hell is happening here?
I need you!

27:20.905 --> 27:22.689
What the hell is happening here?
I need you...

27:23.168 --> 27:24.256
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONCLUDES][WATER SPLASHING]

27:24.430 --> 27:25.866
[LOU BREATHES DEEPLY]

27:28.260 --> 27:30.218
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

27:39.880 --> 27:44.624
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONCLUDES][RINGING]

27:46.844 --> 27:48.672
Lou. How'd it go?

27:50.717 --> 27:51.718
Lou?

27:54.373 --> 27:56.244
Lou?[HAUNTING MUSIC PLAYING]

27:58.638 --> 28:00.727
[WATER SPLASHING]

28:02.816 --> 28:04.818
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

28:11.042 --> 28:12.608
[DOOR CREAKS]

28:17.309 --> 28:21.269
[DOOR CREAKS]

28:29.408 --> 28:30.714
[WHISPERS] Come on.

28:32.411 --> 28:33.717
You're kidding me.

28:41.855 --> 28:44.640
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

28:49.515 --> 28:52.257
[HAUNTING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

28:53.519 --> 28:55.564
[ALARM BLARING]

28:57.349 --> 29:02.658
[INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENT
IN THE DISTANCE]

29:08.926 --> 29:13.539
[HAUNTING MUSIC CONTINUES]

29:26.378 --> 29:30.338
DAVID: Si nequeo. Flectere.

29:31.644 --> 29:37.171
Superos. Si nequeo. Flectere.

29:41.175 --> 29:43.221
[GASPS][HAUNTING MUSIC CONCLUDES]

29:45.484 --> 29:47.529
[INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER TV]

29:50.794 --> 29:52.012
Here we go.

29:52.665 --> 29:55.537
[NEWS THEME PLAYS ON TV]

29:55.624 --> 29:57.191
ANCHOR:
Residents are reminded

29:57.278 --> 30:00.368
state emergency responders
will be spread thin

30:00.455 --> 30:03.328
as acts of civil disobedience
continue.

30:03.545 --> 30:05.504
[CROWD SHOUTING OVER TV]

30:05.678 --> 30:08.855
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

30:09.029 --> 30:10.291
[SIREN WAILING IN BACKGROUND]

30:13.904 --> 30:15.688
Hey, Daddy.PATRICK: Hey.

30:16.080 --> 30:17.951
Thought I'd call you back
and see how you're doing.

30:18.822 --> 30:20.301
Yeah, uh, they...

30:20.911 --> 30:22.216
they sent me out today.

30:22.608 --> 30:23.652
PATRICK: They did?

30:24.001 --> 30:27.482
Well, listen, honey,
congratulations is in order.

30:27.613 --> 30:29.397
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Yeah. Um...

30:31.312 --> 30:35.186
it's been a kinda rough start,
but I'm hanging in there.

30:35.621 --> 30:36.970
Anything you want to talk about?

30:37.057 --> 30:38.842
LOU: No. I don't know.

30:41.801 --> 30:42.758
It was just

30:43.281 --> 30:45.196
a heavy day, you know?
I... I'm drained.

30:45.370 --> 30:49.853
You know, I've seen a lot of...
a lot of shit in my career,

30:49.983 --> 30:52.420
and, um, it's--
You know, that's just...

30:52.638 --> 30:54.335
it just comes with experience

30:54.422 --> 30:56.033
that you don't have
at the moment.

30:56.424 --> 30:58.905
But you're a little warrior.
All right?

30:58.992 --> 31:00.776
You remember
when you were fighting,

31:00.994 --> 31:03.736
and you punched that kid
in the face on a defense,

31:03.823 --> 31:05.216
and then you said you liked it?

31:05.303 --> 31:06.391
You had that look
in your eyes?

31:06.478 --> 31:07.740
You're a warrior. You got this.

31:08.567 --> 31:09.742
Thanks, Dad.

31:10.395 --> 31:12.484
It's just, um, today hit home.

31:12.571 --> 31:15.487
I... I keep, uh...
I keep thinking about Mom.

31:15.879 --> 31:16.923
PATRICK:
Lou, we've been through this.

31:17.315 --> 31:18.446
Not now.

31:18.577 --> 31:19.926
LOU:
I didn't do enough to save her!

31:20.013 --> 31:21.623
PATRICK:
Honey, you were nine years old.

31:21.754 --> 31:23.190
You couldn't have done anything.

31:27.020 --> 31:30.415
[CHILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

31:32.460 --> 31:33.766
What?

31:35.768 --> 31:38.553
Hey, uh... Dad, I, uh...

31:39.946 --> 31:42.035
I gotta get back to work.PATRICK: All right.

31:42.775 --> 31:44.516
I love you, honey. You got this.

31:44.646 --> 31:45.865
LOU: Love you, too.

31:45.996 --> 31:47.258
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

31:50.087 --> 31:54.047
[HORN HONKING][CHILLING MUSIC CONCLUDES]

31:55.614 --> 31:56.658
Hey.

31:57.094 --> 31:58.399
JASON: First day
didn't take you out, huh?

31:58.573 --> 31:59.748
That's good to see.

32:00.488 --> 32:02.882
Well, I don't quit, and I can't
leave my partner hanging.

32:02.969 --> 32:04.188
Where's your clean uniform?

32:04.492 --> 32:07.887
Uh, I think I... I got pranked.
It wasn't in my locker.

32:09.671 --> 32:10.803
It's 'cause you're a newbie.

32:11.108 --> 32:12.848
Mind you, I'm surprised
anyone has time

32:12.979 --> 32:15.068
for that kind of bullshit today.Okay, so you ready to go?

32:15.329 --> 32:17.505
Wow. Okay, so you really wanna
jump back in the ring, huh?

32:18.419 --> 32:19.420
Okay.

32:20.508 --> 32:21.596
Go grab your jump bag.

32:21.683 --> 32:22.946
I'm gonna head around to Dock B,
and load up

32:23.033 --> 32:23.903
and I'll be back for you
in a few.

32:23.990 --> 32:24.991
Okay.

32:25.470 --> 32:26.906
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

32:27.428 --> 32:29.213
[SIRENS WAILING]

32:31.911 --> 32:33.695
Pick up, pick up, pick up!

32:34.218 --> 32:36.002
There you are.
Listen, you son of a--

32:36.089 --> 32:37.612
Don't you fucking hang up
on me again!

32:38.657 --> 32:41.268
I got someone following me,
taking pictures.

32:41.355 --> 32:43.749
If this is one of
your close friends--

32:43.967 --> 32:45.925
[TIRES SCREECHING]Hey! Think about it.

32:46.970 --> 32:49.581
You and I are gonna have
a real fucking problem.

32:51.322 --> 32:52.366
Shit!

32:53.193 --> 32:55.195
Motherfucker
hung up on me again.

32:55.326 --> 32:58.285
He's coming to collect.
[WHEEZES] He's coming to--

32:58.503 --> 33:00.244
For all the real bad
things we done.

33:00.331 --> 33:01.375
VINNY:
That's just the drugs talking.

33:01.506 --> 33:04.335
You don't mean none of that.
Shit, darling,

33:04.813 --> 33:06.163
I would murder half of this city

33:06.337 --> 33:08.339
if they even looked at you
the wrong way.

33:08.469 --> 33:09.601
You know that, right?

33:09.775 --> 33:11.342
Yeah. [EXHALES HEAVILY]Yeah. [EXHALES HEAVILY]

33:11.777 --> 33:13.822
I wanna to go home. [PANTS]

33:13.997 --> 33:15.868
I just got--
I got some business inside.

33:16.129 --> 33:18.436
I just gotta collect real fast.
All right?

33:18.566 --> 33:20.177
Get some money.[EXHALES SHARPLY]

33:21.134 --> 33:25.965
[DOOR RUMBLES][INDISTINCT CHATTER]

33:28.881 --> 33:33.016
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

33:35.583 --> 33:36.976
JASON: Hey.Hey.

33:39.935 --> 33:42.460
There's been a request
for assistance from Old Town.

33:42.547 --> 33:44.244
They're asking for help.
Can you cover it?

33:45.680 --> 33:47.639
Old Town at... at night?

33:47.813 --> 33:50.033
Whoa. Okay. We'll head out.

33:51.251 --> 33:52.296
You good?

33:52.426 --> 33:53.297
Yeah, yeah, I'm good.

33:53.384 --> 33:54.515
Put on your uniform.

33:57.257 --> 33:59.129
That's what
I'm talking about, rookie.

33:59.216 --> 34:01.435
